The article announces the nominations and appointments of two individuals. Sean J. Cooksey is currently serving as General Counsel to U.S. Senator Josh Hawley of Missouri. He has provided advice on various legal issues and has been involved in the U.S. Senate Committee on the Judiciary. Prior to this, he worked as Deputy Chief Counsel for U.S. Senator Ted Cruz and as a litigation associate at Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher LLP.

Shana M. Broussard has been nominated to be a Member of the Federal Election Commission. She currently serves as Counsel to FEC Commissioner Steven T. Walther. She has also worked at the Internal Revenue Service and the Louisiana Attorney Disciplinary Board. Ms. Broussard has received recognition for her performance at the FEC and holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from Dillard University and a Juris Doctor degree from Southern University Law Center.